OL,3,CFree bets coax people into betting
OL,4,Cmore, including problem gamblers `
OL,5,Cstudy
OL,7,FHalf the participants, selected at
OL,8,Frandom, were shown offers of free bets
OL,9,Fand moneyback guarantees on some bets,
OL,10,Fwhile the other half saw no offers.
OL,12,FThese inducements caused participants
OL,13,Fto spend over 10% more and reduced the
OL,14,Fnumber of people opting not to bet by
OL,15,Fa half.
OL,17,FSome bets were intentionally designed
OL,18,Fas "bad bets", offering odds well
OL,19,Fbelow market rates, meaning
OL,20,Fparticipants were better off choosing
OL,21,Fother options or not betting at all.
